&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The ancient texts teach us that the cold hell-fire they call space was not always our home. Once, when we were young and pure, we lived in paradise. But Mankind sinned and we were driven out, to wander amoung the stars for all eternity. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp This is the tale of Mankind after Eden. <br>
<br>
THE WORLD(S)<br>
Mankind lives aboard a single, giant ship called The Ark. There are other planets, some of them less inhabitable than others. Some are peopled, some are not. <br>
<br>
Humans have settled on a few worlds but only in small numbers and they are called Braheyder, or traitors for having abandoned their people to live with strangers. <br>
<br>
<br>
GOVERNMENT/RELIGION<br>
Mankind is ruled by the Council of Nine which draws its members from the different sectors of the societal structure. Below the Council are the various Guilds who supervise the order of all things. <br>
<br>
The Council is based on a religion, Aidmheil (which means Faith), that has been gleaned from the oral histories. All of the council members are Caileadair, religious leaders who guide the Guilds and control the masses. <br>
<br>
There is a second religion, one that is discouraged by the Council of Nine but allowed to remain so long as its followers adhere to the rulings of the Aidmheil. This second religion worships the Mother and Child (Mathair i Leanabhan), a mystical pair who supposedly look after their followers, protecting them from harm and granting them good fortune. <br>
<br>
LANGUAGES<br>
Mankind has slowly distilled one language that is a piecemeal of several others. The different classes also have very different accents and slang, some of them using more of the original languages than others. <br>
<br>
There is also a universal language amoung the spacing peoples known as Common. It has an odd syntax and uses no contractions. <br>
<br>
CAILEADAIR<br>
The Caileadair are born in a very specific and ceremonial fashion. They have special powers conferred on them through the crystal which has fused with their bodies. The crystal would normally kill a person but if introduced while a person is still in an embryonic state doesn’t produce the deadly reaction. <br>
<br>
The Caileadair are created by selecting the most promising women (those who already display “gifts”) who are then impregnated and fed a mixture of powdered crystal and blood from the current Caileadair. The blood slows the mother’s reaction to the crystal allowing her to carry the child to term, while the crystal fuses with the embryo. <br>
<br>
In almost every case the children born are male (a fact which is attributed divine significance). On very, very rare occasions a female child has been born. These are not considered Caileadair but called Fadeyr instead. <br>
<br>
FADEYR<br>
There have only been three Fadeyr born in the past five hundred years. They are considered to be heretics by the Caileadair since they invariably end up as followers of Mathair i Leanabhan. <br>
<br>
Fadeyr are stronger than Caileadair and therefore much feared by the Council. Fadeyr also tend to be much loved by the people. <br>
<br>
THE HORDE<br>
Considered by many to be mythical, The Horde is what supposedly drove Mankind out of Eden. There are corresponding legends amoung the other spacing peoples that indicate that The Horde might be real. However, since The Horde hasn’t been seen in centuries many believe that it has been destroyed or never existed in the first place. <br>
